      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>it's not just that i don't like the look of it though. i've noticed it's the same kind of pattern in a bunch of different brands lately. like, it's a very specific geometric alignment. if it was just a matter of taste, i wouldn't feel this heavy, compliant vibe whenever i'm around it. you mentioned how patterns impact mood... do you think it's possible for companies to use specific visual frequencies or geometry to influence how people behave in public? like, a way to make us more passive without us even realizing it?",
